dcterms:description: A dataset of 22,467 2D mazes generated for testing the performance of the generalized value iteration network (GVIN) in planning tasks.
dcterms:title: 2D Mazes

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset consisting of 10000 irregular graphs, each containing 100 nodes, used to evaluate the performance of GVIN in handling irregular graph structures.
dcterms:title: Irregular Graphs

dcterms:description: The Minnesota highway map contains 2642 nodes representing intersections and 6606 edges representing roads, used for evaluating GVIN's performance in real-world scenarios.
dcterms:title: Minnesota Highway Map

dcterms:description: The New York City street map contains 5069 nodes representing intersections and 13368 edges representing roads, used for evaluating GVIN's performance in real-world scenarios.
dcterms:title: New York City Street Map
